  "body": "**ðŸ§ Motivation**\r\n`MerkleProof.processMultiProof` only accepts parameters stored in `calldata`.\r\nLeaves are often constructed by the calling code (in `memory`), and sometimes even the proof.\r\nFunctions need to be created for each use case\r\n\r\n**ðŸ“ Details**\r\n## Current\r\n#### processMultiProof\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction processMultiProof(\r\n        bytes32[] calldata proof,\r\n        bool[] calldata proofFlags,\r\n        bytes32[] calldata leaves\r\n) ...\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Proposed\r\nIn line with the approach taken to solve this problem by `MerkleProof.processProof` & `MerkleProof.processProofCalldata` I suggest that there be three variants of the function.\r\n\r\n#### processMultiProofCalldata\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction processMultiProofCalldata(\r\n        bytes32[] calldata proof,\r\n        bool[] calldata proofFlags,\r\n        bytes32[] calldata leaves\r\n) ...\r\n```\r\nMost gas efficient, least flexible\r\nSimply a rename `MerkleProof.processMultiProof` -> `MerkleProof.processMultiProofCalldata`\r\n\r\n\r\n#### processMultiProofCalldataProof\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction processMultiProofCalldata(\r\n        bytes32[] calldata proof,\r\n        bool[] calldata proofFlags,\r\n        bytes32[] memory leaves\r\n) ...\r\n```\r\nThis function has the correct gas/flexibility tradeoff for many applications\r\n_Note. Probably not the best name_\r\n\r\n\r\n#### processMultiProof\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction processMultiProof(\r\n        bytes32[] memory proof,\r\n        bool[] memory proofFlags,\r\n        bytes32[] memory leaves\r\n) ...\r\n```\r\nMost flexible, but least gas efficient\r\n",
